name: UniversalRouter
description: This is a universal router contract that is used to execute specified command sequences and dispatch them to the corresponding contracts. It supports an optional transaction deadline to prevent transactions from timing out and provides additional security features.

name: UniswapV3Factory
description: This is a smart contract called UniswapV3Factory, which deploys and manages Uniswap V3 pools and controls the ownership and protocol fees of the pools. It implements the IUniswapV3Factory interface and has methods to create pools, set the owner, and enable fee amounts. It uses mappings to keep track of created pools and their parameters, and deploys the pools using the UniswapV3PoolDeployer contract. The owner of the contract can enable specific fee amounts and corresponding tick spacings to be used for pool creation. Overall, the contract enables the creation and management of Uniswap V3 pools in a decentralized and trustless manner.

name: Multicall2
description: The Multicall2 contract allows for the aggregation of results from multiple read-only function calls in a single transaction. It includes helper functions for fetching information about the current Ethereum block, such as the block number, hash, timestamp, and gas limit. The contract provides the aggregate() and blockAndAggregate() functions for executing multiple function calls and returning their results, either with or without block information. Additionally, the contract includes the tryAggregate() and tryBlockAndAggregate() functions for executing function calls and returning their results, with an option to require success.

name: ProxyAdmin
description: The ProxyAdmin contract serves as the admin for a TransparentUpgradeableProxy contract. It includes functions for retrieving the implementation and admin addresses of a proxy, changing the admin address of a proxy, and upgrading the implementation of a proxy. These functions can only be called by the owner of the ProxyAdmin contract. It is used as an auxiliary contract to provide upgradeable functionality in a safe and secure manner.

name: TickLens
description: This is a smart contract called TickLens, which implements the ITickLens interface. It provides a method to retrieve populated ticks from a Uniswap V3 pool bitmap, based on the tick bitmap index. This method first fetches the tick bitmap, then calculates the number of populated ticks in it. Finally, it fetches populated tick data, including tick ID, net liquidity, and gross liquidity, and returns it as a list of structs called PopulatedTick.

name: Quoter
description: This contract provides quotes for trades, allowing the expected input or output amount for a given trade to be obtained without executing the trade. It implements the IQuoter interface and provides four methods: quoteExactInputSingle, quoteExactInput, quoteExactOutputSingle, and quoteExactOutput, which can return the input or output amount. quoteExactInputSingle and quoteExactOutputSingle methods accept two tokens, a fee rate, and an amount, and return the corresponding output or input amount. quoteExactInput and quoteExactOutput methods take a trade path and an amount, and perform a series of exact input or output exchanges on the path, ultimately returning the output or input amount. When performing exchanges, the contract follows the logic of the Uniswap V3 protocol and calculates the trade fee rate through querying the pools. If the query fails, zero is returned.

name: SwapRouter
description: This is a smart contract called SwapRouter, which facilitates stateless execution of swaps against Uniswap V3. It allows for swapping between tokens within a liquidity pool and across multiple pools. The contract interfaces with Uniswap V3 through the IUniswapV3Pool interface and performs swaps via input and output amounts. The contract also handles payments with fees and verifies callback functions for swaps. It includes methods for exact input and exact output swaps, as well as internal methods for performing these swaps. Additionally, the contract utilizes several libraries for path decoding, pool address calculation, callback validation, and more.

name: NFTDescriptor
description: Constructs a token URI for NFTs representing Uniswap V3 liquidity positions with token, pool, and position details.

name: NonfungibleTokenPositionDescriptor
description: Manages token URI generation for Uniswap V3 positions, handles token ratio priority, and allows flipping token ratios.

name: TransparentUpgradeableProxy
description: A proxy contract managing upgrades, admin changes, and implementation calls, with payable fallback and receive functions.

name: NonfungiblePositionManager
description: Manages Uniswap V3 positions as NFTs with minting, burning, transferring and collecting functions.

name: V3Migrator
description: Burns v2 liquidity tokens and mints a v3 position NFT with slippage protection and specified parameters.

name: QuoterV2
description: Calculates swap amounts for exact input/output without execution and returns pool data after swap.

name: SwapRouter02
description: Performs swaps across v2 and v3 pools with self-permit, multicall and pool initialization features.

name: Permit2
description: Enables signature-based approvals and transfers of ERC-20 tokens.
